STO,
Rgr, sounds good, thank you!
The next thing I would investigate for connectivity issues with SSDS and CDLMS is the following:
1. Are you or have you been recording DX?
a. If so, how long are your recording blocks when you do record DX?
b. How often do you offload and delete your DX files?
2. Logon as root and open a terminal window
a. type the command "bdf" 

1. Report the capacity data displayed
2. If your C2PMAINT HDD is anywhere near 80% full, CDLMS will become unstable
b. Run the 4.10.1 OFF-LOADING AND DELETION OF AUDIT FILES procedure from the SUM
1. The user auditing should actually be turned off. After a software load, by default it used to be "ON" 
 and should be turned OFF. Audit files fill up the drive.
3. From the CDLMS SUM
1. Conduct the offloading procedures for DX 

2. Conduct transferring of corefiles to DAT or CD
3. Remove Core and Log files
4. Remove DX files 

4. Once you have conducted the above, rerun Step 2 through 2.a.1.
5. Logon as root and open a terminal window, if not already open
a. type the command "vme_config" 

b. when prompted to overwrite EEPROM data, type y then enter
c. It is good to run this procedure whenever you have removed or replaced the HP 744, any CCA in that VME or if the 744 seems a bit sluggish
6. Cold load CDLMS, restore link operations and report status
Very Respectfully,
ETC Fogleberg, James D.
